  "prompt": "I'm tired, but I cant sleep, why is that?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why you're tired but can't sleep:\n\n1. Stress and anxiety\n- Racing thoughts\n- Worry about work, personal issues, or the future\n\n2. Poor sleep hygiene\n- Irregular sleep schedule\n- Using electronic devices before bed\n- Caffeine or alcohol consumption late in the day\n\n3. Medical conditions\n- Insomnia\n- Sleep apnea\n- Restless leg syndrome\n- Depression or other mental health issues\n\n4. Environmental factors\n- Uncomfortable room temperature\n- Noise\n- Light\n- Uncomfortable bed or pillow\n\n5. Physiological reasons\n- Hormonal changes\n- Chronic pain\n- Medications\n- Irregular circadian rhythm\n\n6. Lifestyle factors\n- Lack of exercise\n- Irregular eating patterns\n- Shift work\n- Jet lag\n\nRecommendations:\n- Create a consistent sleep routine\n- Avoid screens before bedtime\n- Practice relaxation techniques\n- Limit caffeine and alcohol\n- Exercise regularly\n- Consult a healthcare professional if sleep issues persist\n\nIf sleeplessness is ongoing, it's best to speak with a doctor to rule out underlying health issues.",
